            <title><![CDATA[The Week's Top Tips For Doom: The Dark Ages, Clair Obscur, Oblivion Remastered, And More]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/doom-dark-ages-wolf-statues-oblivion-remastered-tips-1851782186</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/the-weeks-top-tips-for-doom-the-dark-ages-clair-obscur-oblivion-remastered-and-more.1198431/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/doom-dark-ages-wolf-statues-oblivion-remastered-tips-1851782186<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="3891b373425b74f304fdbb72131fa3e8" data-recommend-id="image://3891b373425b74f304fdbb72131fa3e8" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->id Software / George Yang / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Sandfall Interactive / Justin Clark / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Bethesda / Brandon Morgan / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Sandfall Interactive / George Yang / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Sandfall Interactive / Justin Clark / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Ubisoft / Justin Clark / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Activision / Brandon Morgan / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Bethesda / Brandon Morgan / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->id Software / George Yang / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Mercury Steam</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3891b373425b74f304fdbb72131fa3e8" data-recommend-id="image://3891b373425b74f304fdbb72131fa3e8" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Whether you need help locating some of <em>Doom: The Dark Ages, </em>want to make the most of Verso in <em>Clair Obscur: Expedition 33</em>, or you’d just like to learn some essential things that <em>Oblivion Remastered </em>doesn’t tell you, read on, we’ve got all this info and more.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="4aabe136ae9bfef02b01bbef06a6cf2f" data-recommend-id="image://4aabe136ae9bfef02b01bbef06a6cf2f" data-format="jpg" data-width="1366" data-height="768" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The player stands before a glowing crystal." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The player stands before a glowing crystal." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->id Software / George Yang / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4aabe136ae9bfef02b01bbef06a6cf2f" data-recommend-id="image://4aabe136ae9bfef02b01bbef06a6cf2f" data-format="jpg" data-width="1366" data-height="768" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The player stands before a glowing crystal." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Aside from a more ambitious narrative scope, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/games/doom-the-dark-ages&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/games/doom-the-dark-ages"><em>Doom: The Dark Ages</em></a></span> also introduced semi open-world areas where objectives and secrets are a bit more spread out. “The Kar’Thul Marshes,” the fifteenth mission in the game, is the third of these, after “<span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/doom-dark-ages-siege-part-1-lion-statues-knight-ruby-1851780496&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/doom-dark-ages-siege-part-1-lion-statues-knight-ruby-1851780496">The Siege Part One</a></span>” and “<span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/doom-dark-ages-lion-statues-sorcerer-statue-ancestral-1851780714&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/doom-dark-ages-lion-statues-sorcerer-statue-ancestral-1851780714">Ancestral Forge</a></span>.” - George Yang <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/doom-dark-ages-wolf-statue-locations-wraithstone-1851781357&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/doom-dark-ages-wolf-statue-locations-wraithstone-1851781357">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="22a7ce9aa99a5f68faee8a1b80e56c68" data-recommend-id="image://22a7ce9aa99a5f68faee8a1b80e56c68" data-format="jpg" data-width="1888" data-height="1062" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Verso and Maelle." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Verso and Maelle." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sandfall Interactive / Justin Clark / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="22a7ce9aa99a5f68faee8a1b80e56c68" data-recommend-id="image://22a7ce9aa99a5f68faee8a1b80e56c68" data-format="jpg" data-width="1888" data-height="1062" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Verso and Maelle." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Note: <em>This guide contains light spoilers for the end of Act I of </em>Clair Obscur: Expedition 33</p><p>It’s Act II. The plot thickens. Big Daddy Gollum’s still wreaking havoc on your damn team, and the role of Gustave will now be played by Clive Rosfiel—er, Verso. Despite trading the Devil of Hell’s Kitchen for <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://youtube.com/shorts/FnCzW3SHeWY?si=1-UlnohHlpfMTCeJ&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://youtube.com/shorts/FnCzW3SHeWY?si=1-UlnohHlpfMTCeJ" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Final Fantasy VIII</em>’s number one simp</a></span>, it’s a relatively easy transition, but not one without its quirks—and a whole new gimmick to learn. Once you learn that gimmick, and get into some of the deep skills in his tree, though, Verso can become the linchpin of your team. We’ll show you how.  - Justin Clark <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-verso-perfection-letters-1851781828&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-verso-perfection-letters-1851781828">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="476f49ec737f767d01294972a1a57033" data-recommend-id="image://476f49ec737f767d01294972a1a57033" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The ruins of Fanacasecul outside the Imperial City in Oblivion Remastered." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The ruins of Fanacasecul outside the Imperial City in Oblivion Remastered." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Bethesda / Brandon Morgan / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="476f49ec737f767d01294972a1a57033" data-recommend-id="image://476f49ec737f767d01294972a1a57033" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The ruins of Fanacasecul outside the Imperial City in Oblivion Remastered." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>If you’re playing a Mage-type class in <em>Oblivion Remastered</em>—who doesn’t want to toss fireballs and smack people with a lightning-infused backhand?—then you’ll need to prioritize improving the Destruction skill. It’s a key skill that turns the average magic-wielding wannabe into Merlin. With the right magical artifact, you could give the most powerful spell-slingers a run for their money, and it all starts with the lady in the lake. In this case, the lady is a ring. It’s just…a ring. - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/oblivion-remastered-ring-of-destruction-swim-water-1851781735&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/oblivion-remastered-ring-of-destruction-swim-water-1851781735">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="924e5a7bc97e0a9e8dd4e87e0da07cb8" data-recommend-id="image://924e5a7bc97e0a9e8dd4e87e0da07cb8" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Lune stands before Demineur" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Lune stands before Demineur" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sandfall Interactive / George Yang / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="924e5a7bc97e0a9e8dd4e87e0da07cb8" data-recommend-id="image://924e5a7bc97e0a9e8dd4e87e0da07cb8" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Lune stands before Demineur" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>In <em>Clair Obscur: Expedition 33</em>, you’ll come across quests where you can help out the expedition’s enemies, Nevrons. While most Nevrons are hostile, there are a few that’ll ask for help. One early Nevron quest takes place in the Flying Waters dungeon with a fellow named Demineur.  - George Yang <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-lune-weapon-demineur-mine-1851781921&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-lune-weapon-demineur-mine-1851781921">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="e2d0126c3735d669e3c4beaac48157db" data-recommend-id="image://e2d0126c3735d669e3c4beaac48157db" data-format="jpg" data-width="1894" data-height="1065" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Verso stands defiantly before the Dualliste." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Verso stands defiantly before the Dualliste." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sandfall Interactive / Justin Clark / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="e2d0126c3735d669e3c4beaac48157db" data-recommend-id="image://e2d0126c3735d669e3c4beaac48157db" data-format="jpg" data-width="1894" data-height="1065" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Verso stands defiantly before the Dualliste." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>You might’ve caught a few vibes here and there that the good folks at Sandfall might’ve had a <em>Souls </em>game or two on the brain while designing <em>Clair Obscur.</em> But right around here is the point where reasonable doubt gets kicked off a skyscraper, because the Dualliste is the most <em>Souls-</em>game shit ever. It’s a lot of long combos, a second phase, and a lot—and I do mean <em>a lot</em>—of dying.  - Justin Clark <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-dualliste-phase-2-verso-1851781495&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-dualliste-phase-2-verso-1851781495">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="84615e1de68590551dd37aa8acd3539e" data-recommend-id="image://84615e1de68590551dd37aa8acd3539e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Yasuke walks up to the wise and other NPCs." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Yasuke walks up to the wise and other NPCs." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ubisoft / Justin Clark / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="84615e1de68590551dd37aa8acd3539e" data-recommend-id="image://84615e1de68590551dd37aa8acd3539e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Yasuke walks up to the wise and other NPCs." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>You know, Naoe and Yasuke have been killing a whole lot of people lately. Maybe this time, given this mission’s all about two diametrically opposed political factions trying to come to an agreement, they really should dial back down on the violent rhetoric, reach across the aisle, and let diplomacy take its course. - Justin Clark <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-wise-boss-yasuke-the-messenger-1851781455&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-wise-boss-yasuke-the-messenger-1851781455">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="501dae0f870443cc6e1b3e7a1a82f10c" data-recommend-id="image://501dae0f870443cc6e1b3e7a1a82f10c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The side inspection animation for the Ladra SMG in Black Ops 6." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The side inspection animation for the Ladra SMG in Black Ops 6." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Activision / Brandon Morgan / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="501dae0f870443cc6e1b3e7a1a82f10c" data-recommend-id="image://501dae0f870443cc6e1b3e7a1a82f10c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The side inspection animation for the Ladra SMG in Black Ops 6." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>One of the most interesting additions joining the fray in <em>Call of Duty: Black Ops 6 Season 3 Reloaded </em>(what a mouthful!) is the Ladra submachine gun. It’s a fast-firing SMG reminiscent of the Tec-9. But with such a high rate of fire comes a lack of control, which we’ll aim to resolve with the right attachments. While I’m not the best player, I can hold my own, and I know how to build a loadout to suit my purposes, especially in CQB. As proof, I offer you a sweet Ladra loadout in <em>Black Ops 6</em> and <em>Warzone </em>that saw me achieve nearly 500 kills fast! - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/call-duty-black-ops-6-warzone-wz-ladra-attachments-1851781095&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/call-duty-black-ops-6-warzone-wz-ladra-attachments-1851781095">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="7755631169b9a543d4db84284bb71042" data-recommend-id="image://7755631169b9a543d4db84284bb71042" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The spires of a Daedric Realm in Oblivion Remastered" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The spires of a Daedric Realm in Oblivion Remastered" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Bethesda / Brandon Morgan / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="7755631169b9a543d4db84284bb71042" data-recommend-id="image://7755631169b9a543d4db84284bb71042" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The spires of a Daedric Realm in Oblivion Remastered" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>As you exit the prologue sewers in <em>Oblivion Remastered</em>, you’re greeted by a whole lot of nothing. There are ruins across the water, a small abandoned dock down the hill, and behind you, an entire city. But where do you go, what do you do, and why should you care about delivering a necklace of all things? There’s a lot the game doesn’t tell you, and we aim to fix that. - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/oblivion-remastered-selling-stolen-goods-scaling-gates-1851781929&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/oblivion-remastered-selling-stolen-goods-scaling-gates-1851781929">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="c71406792b46106aae52769ec2e1cb81" data-recommend-id="image://c71406792b46106aae52769ec2e1cb81" data-format="jpg" data-width="1336" data-height="752" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A wolf statue glows before the Doom Slayer." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A wolf statue glows before the Doom Slayer." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->id Software / George Yang / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="c71406792b46106aae52769ec2e1cb81" data-recommend-id="image://c71406792b46106aae52769ec2e1cb81" data-format="jpg" data-width="1336" data-height="752" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A wolf statue glows before the Doom Slayer." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure></div><div><figure id="" data-id="b276130c7a0a2a8f4af9062c81e4c0ce" data-recommend-id="image://b276130c7a0a2a8f4af9062c81e4c0ce" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The protagonist and NPC of Blades of Fire stand side-by-side." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The protagonist and NPC of Blades of Fire stand side-by-side." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Mercury Steam</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="b276130c7a0a2a8f4af9062c81e4c0ce" data-recommend-id="image://b276130c7a0a2a8f4af9062c81e4c0ce" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The protagonist and NPC of Blades of Fire stand side-by-side." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Developer Mercury Steam is perhaps best known for 2010’s <em>Castlevania: Lords of Shadow </em>and, more recently, <em>Metroid Dread</em>. The studio’s newest game, <em>Blades of Fire</em>, is a tough action-adventure RPG with Soulslike elements and a surprisingly in-depth weapon-forging mini-game. - George Yang <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/blades-of-fire-weapon-switch-outline-difficulty-options-1851781897&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/blades-of-fire-weapon-switch-outline-difficulty-options-1851781897">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
